          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-12916 osd-ldiskfs: add delayed allocation support",
        "message": "LU-12916 osd-ldiskfs: add delayed allocation support\n\nThis is a prototype to add delayed allocation support in ldiskfs.\n\nIt just copies data into page cache. It does not do block\nallocation and just mark the buffer head as delayed and dirty.\n\nIf good full extent check is enabled, it will try to find\ncontiguous dirty pages in the page mapping and build a good full\nextent write to the underlying RAID disk system.\n\nTODO: Scanning the page mapping for a good full extent write may\nbe too expensive. Maybe we can imporve it by using Ext4 extent\nstatus tree (@extent_status) to detect full extent write?\n\nTest-Parameters: forbuildonly\nSigned-off-by: Qian Yingjin <qian@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: Ide819709406696467cea06205571ed0950df900e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
